  "description": [
    "PAGE 2 EDITORIALS US And Vietnam With our support of the Viet nam administration firmly est ablished we were suddenly at a loss to ascertain what position to adopt during its recent over throw by revolutionaries We be lieve that there were many like us Events turn so fast in our present world that we often are left in a state of mental chaos We did know that the Diem regime was antiCommunist but now we believe that was not enough The American press seems pretty well assured that the Diem regime was despotic too There were Americans who were aware of this beforehand and none of us would have been caught unawares if we had been cognizant of the Oct 8 Senate address by U S Sen Vance Hartke of Indiana Following are excerpts from his talk For the sixth time a Budd hist monk has voiced protest of oppression by the regime of Ngo Dinh Diem in South Viet nam in the most drastic mann er possible by becoming a flaming torch in suicide No one can deny the depth of convic tion which has driven desper ate people to such terrible acts in order to draw the"
